\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 2. One-Line Summary\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 PR War Room is a CLI tool that runs a multi-agent AI review flow on a GitHub pull request before human review, with the goal of finding, ranking, deduplicating, and optionally fixing issues that a human reviewer would likely comment on.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 3. Problem Statement\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Developers increasingly use AI while writing code, but human reviewers still frequently find issues in pull requests after the developer has already completed their own self-review.\
This creates avoidable review cycles, slows down merge time, and leaves developers dependent on human reviewers to catch issues that could have been identified earlier.\
Existing AI code review tools are often too generic. They produce noisy comments, miss team-specific patterns, and rarely include a robust verification loop.\
The product should reduce the chance that a human reviewer finds meaningful feedback that the AI did not surface first.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 4. Product Goal\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 The goal is not to replace human review.\
The goal is to make every PR significantly more review-ready before it reaches a human reviewer.\
The tool should:\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\partightenfactor0
\ls1\ilvl0\cf0 \kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	1	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Ingest a GitHub PR.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	2	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Build a high-quality review context.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	3	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Run multiple independent AI review agents.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	4	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Normalize all findings into a strict schema.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	5	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Deduplicate overlapping findings.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	6	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Use a skeptic / evidence-checking step to reduce false positives.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	7	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Use an LLM-as-a-judge step to rank findings by usefulness and likelihood of human review comments.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	8	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Produce a short, actionable report.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	9	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Optionally generate code fixes as local patches.\
\ls1\ilvl0\kerning1\expnd0\expndtw0 \outl0\strokewidth0 {\listtext	10	}\expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Eventually evaluate itself against historical human PR comments.\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0
\cf3 \strokec3 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

